WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:03.062
<i>Previously on</i> aMC's
"Better Call Saul"...

2
00:00:03.080 --> 00:00:05.290
Free.
I'll shoot the spot for free.

3
00:00:05.357 --> 00:00:06.376
For free?

4
00:00:06.444 --> 00:00:07.813
You're losing money.

5
00:00:07.861 --> 00:00:09.180
My brother is sick.

6
00:00:09.228 --> 00:00:11.149
He's making mistakes
with his clients.

7
00:00:11.204 --> 00:00:12.798
You're not gonna
do anything. are you?

8
00:00:12.923 --> 00:00:14.157
To new beginnings.

9
00:00:14.228 --> 00:00:16.759
I need to see Dr. Cruz
as soon as possible.

10
00:00:16.797 --> 00:00:18.907
The man killed for helping
the truck driver.

11
00:00:18.955 --> 00:00:20.290
You are trying
to correct something

12
00:00:20.337 --> 00:00:21.462
which cannot be corrected.

13
00:00:21.510 --> 00:00:23.282
Hector wants to use
my dad's business.

14
00:00:23.352 --> 00:00:26.532
If you manage to pull this off
and switch those pills.

15
00:00:26.620 --> 00:00:27.751
switch them back.

16
00:00:27.929 --> 00:00:29.853
I'm gonna need
one more thing from you.

17
00:00:30.785 --> 00:00:34.637
[Thumping]

18
00:00:36.776 --> 00:00:38.916
[Lock clanking]

19
00:00:41.880 --> 00:00:43.685
[Dog barking in distance]

20
00:00:51.819 --> 00:00:53.539
Let there be light.

21
00:00:54.164 --> 00:00:56.086
And then there was light.

22
00:00:59.046 --> 00:01:00.139
Geez.

23
00:01:00.187 --> 00:01:02.492
Will you look at this...

24
00:01:06.632 --> 00:01:08.882
That's where
your mom used to work.

25
00:01:09.484 --> 00:01:11.226
Right back there.
doin' the books.

26
00:01:11.301 --> 00:01:13.156
Yeah. Whatever.

27
00:01:17.943 --> 00:01:20.170
Hey. remember when
we used to ditch fourth

28
00:01:20.231 --> 00:01:21.411
come in the back door?

29
00:01:21.499 --> 00:01:23.748
Tell your folks
it was a free period.

30
00:01:23.849 --> 00:01:25.576
O'dell's algebra two.

31
00:01:25.712 --> 00:01:27.201
[ Laughing ]
Mr. O'Dell.

32
00:01:27.374 --> 00:01:29.443
Man. that guy was a butthole.

33
00:01:29.836 --> 00:01:32.217
And your mom. you know. I think
she knew we were skipping.

34
00:01:32.281 --> 00:01:33.741
But she'd always
stop what she was doing

35
00:01:33.788 --> 00:01:36.092
And gimme a pack of
little debbie's. Ahh.

36
00:01:36.186 --> 00:01:37.529
Think all those little debbie's

37
00:01:37.608 --> 00:01:39.273
put them out of business.

38
00:01:39.321 --> 00:01:40.389
[Chuckles]

39
00:01:40.437 --> 00:01:42.383
Hey. how'd you get up there
when you were a kid?

40
00:01:42.445 --> 00:01:44.943
couple of milk crates. you know?

41
00:01:48.054 --> 00:01:49.887
Ohh.

42
00:01:51.038 --> 00:01:53.137
[Rattling]

43
00:01:57.372 --> 00:01:59.208
[Sniffles]
All right.

44
00:02:02.021 --> 00:02:05.216
No. No. No.
Nope.

45
00:02:05.347 --> 00:02:06.630
Ah.

46
00:02:06.708 --> 00:02:09.504
[Inhales sharply]
Boom.

47
00:02:09.998 --> 00:02:11.982
Indian head penny.
All right?

48
00:02:12.098 --> 00:02:13.435
That's worth about three bucks.

49
00:02:13.483 --> 00:02:15.591
We polish it up.
run the coin game...

50
00:02:15.750 --> 00:02:17.652
Nice.
We get 150 bucks. easy.

51
00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:18.709
$150?

52
00:02:18.757 --> 00:02:20.941
We got a $110
for a plain vanilla half dollar.

53
00:02:20.996 --> 00:02:22.847
This... this is
actually rare.

54
00:02:22.895 --> 00:02:24.113
I mean. you can see it.

55
00:02:24.323 --> 00:02:26.807
- $300. easy.
- Oh. $300?

56
00:02:26.855 --> 00:02:28.855
- Me likey.
- Yeah.

57
00:02:28.948 --> 00:02:29.948
Now you're gonna tell me

58
00:02:29.996 --> 00:02:32.472
What your coin collection
was doin' up there.

59
00:02:32.746 --> 00:02:34.144
Uh...

60
00:02:35.026 --> 00:02:36.086
[Sighs]

61
00:02:36.134 --> 00:02:37.530
It's a long story.

62
00:02:37.585 --> 00:02:41.797
Um...
Let's get outta here.

63
00:02:45.016 --> 00:02:47.960
[Siren wails. flashlight clicks]

64
00:02:48.467 --> 00:02:50.367
[Wailing continues]

65
00:02:50.446 --> 00:02:52.104
[Dog barking in distance]

66
00:02:52.175 --> 00:02:53.987
All right. Now.
Let's hit it.

67
00:02:54.071 --> 00:02:56.112
No. there might be another one.

68
00:02:56.414 --> 00:02:57.674
All right.

69
00:02:57.821 --> 00:02:59.053
Then give.

70
00:02:59.132 --> 00:03:01.151
What's the deal with the coins?

71
00:03:01.948 --> 00:03:03.518
[Chuckles]

72
00:03:05.368 --> 00:03:06.588
Well. uh...

73
00:03:06.768 --> 00:03:09.284
[Inhales sharply]
I was what?

74
00:03:09.659 --> 00:03:11.112
Uh. 12 or so?

75
00:03:11.166 --> 00:03:12.706
I was working the register.

76
00:03:12.862 --> 00:03:15.846
Guy comes in.
buys a box of ivory flakes

77
00:03:15.899 --> 00:03:19.745
and a sixer of old style.

78
00:03:21.667 --> 00:03:24.953
He pays
with a couple bucks and...

79
00:03:25.424 --> 00:03:26.689
This.

80
00:03:26.910 --> 00:03:29.258
The second I see it.
I know what it is...

81
00:03:29.306 --> 00:03:31.500
It's a George Washington Silver.

82
00:03:31.639 --> 00:03:34.563
I tell my dad.
"pop. this quarter is rare.

83
00:03:34.611 --> 00:03:37.524
It's worth
four bucks."

84
00:03:37.868 --> 00:03:39.524
Barely get the words
outta my mouth...

85
00:03:39.572 --> 00:03:42.469
He hightails it outta here
to give it back.

86
00:03:42.672 --> 00:03:43.828
He can't find the guy.

87
00:03:43.891 --> 00:03:45.992
so he tapes it
to the side of the register...

88
00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:48.274
he's hoping [Chuckling]
that this guy

89
00:03:48.322 --> 00:03:51.891
will come back
so we can return it.

90
00:03:52.368 --> 00:03:54.133
After about a week.
he starts talking about

91
00:03:54.181 --> 00:03:56.180
Givin' it to father mahoney
for the poor box.

92
00:03:56.270 --> 00:03:58.071
So I make it disappear.

93
00:03:58.285 --> 00:03:59.805
And after that.
every day after school.

94
00:03:59.852 --> 00:04:00.914
I'm checking the till.

95
00:04:00.967 --> 00:04:02.155
You know.
something catches my eye.

96
00:04:02.202 --> 00:04:03.071
I stick it in the box.

97
00:04:03.105 --> 00:04:05.133
Put it up there for good luck.

98
00:04:05.281 --> 00:04:06.742
[Clears throat]

99
00:04:06.882 --> 00:04:08.677
So much for good luck.

100
00:04:10.602 --> 00:04:13.135
It was a cryin' shame
they lost this place.

101
00:04:13.656 --> 00:04:15.055
[Chuckling]
They never shoulda bought it

102
00:04:15.102 --> 00:04:16.343
in the first place.

103
00:04:16.503 --> 00:04:18.499
My dad didn't have it in him.

104
00:04:18.888 --> 00:04:20.151
Whaddya mean?

105
00:04:20.442 --> 00:04:22.044
Your folks worked so hard.

106
00:04:22.153 --> 00:04:23.286
Yeah. they worked hard!

107
00:04:23.356 --> 00:04:26.380
They worked a lotta hours
for a lotta years.

108
00:04:26.458 --> 00:04:27.692
For nothin'.

109
00:04:27.742 --> 00:04:29.849
I dunno. jimmy.
He had a lotta customers.

110
00:04:29.903 --> 00:04:30.903
Everybody liked him.

111
00:04:30.976 --> 00:04:33.896
Everybody liked him
'cause he was a soft touch.

112
00:04:33.981 --> 00:04:35.005
You know?

113
00:04:35.060 --> 00:04:37.309
Every deadbeat in
the neighborhood owed him money.

114
00:04:37.357 --> 00:04:38.864
You come in here
with a sob story.

115
00:04:38.929 --> 00:04:41.630
you leave with a pat on the back
and a gallon of milk.

116
00:04:41.749 --> 00:04:43.380
He... he coulda
made it work.

117
00:04:43.490 --> 00:04:45.552
He coulda sold beer
and cigarettes

118
00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:46.926
to the kids
from Mary-Margaret's.

119
00:04:46.974 --> 00:04:50.271
but [Chuckles] oh. no. not him.

120
00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:53.677
He was never
gonna do what he had to do.

121
00:04:58.571 --> 00:05:01.471
[Siren wailing]

122
00:05:01.731 --> 00:05:03.401
[Clears throat]

123
00:05:04.032 --> 00:05:05.892
How'd you know
there'd be another?

124
00:05:06.042 --> 00:05:07.126
[Scoffs]

125
00:05:07.271 --> 00:05:10.271
[Dog barking in distance]

126
00:05:10.584 --> 00:05:11.790
Oh.

127
00:05:12.077 --> 00:05:13.631
Banquet's over.

128
00:05:14.796 --> 00:05:18.170
Those conventioneers
been talking farm equipment

129
00:05:18.218 --> 00:05:20.178
for 10 hours straight...

130
00:05:20.474 --> 00:05:22.374
Now they wanna party.

131
00:05:24.139 --> 00:05:26.898
Gonna be a big night. my friend.
Whaddya say?

132
00:05:27.086 --> 00:05:29.452
Time to get moving?
Let's go.

133
