contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

134
00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:47.577
<font color=#FF00FF>*BETTER CALL SAUL</font> 
<font color=#00FF00>Season 03 Episode 08</font>
 Episode Title: <font color=#FFFF00>"Slip"</font>

135
00:05:56.307 --> 00:06:00.158
[vehicle approaches]

136
00:06:02.589 --> 00:06:04.019
[Breaks squeal]

137
00:06:04.127 --> 00:06:05.927
[Gearshift clicks]

138
00:06:05.975 --> 00:06:07.637
[Engine shuts off]

139
00:06:08.132 --> 00:06:09.702
[Keys jingle]

140
00:06:30.843 --> 00:06:33.643
[Trunk squeaks]

141
00:06:41.664 --> 00:06:43.834
[Sighs]

142
00:07:09.592 --> 00:07:16.302
[Wind rushing. insects chirping]

143
00:07:30.880 --> 00:07:34.450
[Metal detector beeping]

144
00:07:46.683 --> 00:07:49.785
[Metal detector beeps loudly]

145
00:08:07.249 --> 00:08:09.522
[Clatters]

146
00:08:10.709 --> 00:08:14.569
♪♪

147
00:08:16.307 --> 00:08:18.807
[metal detector beeping]

148
00:08:19.763 --> 00:08:23.631
♪♪

149
00:08:29.873 --> 00:08:33.482
♪♪

150
00:08:34.867 --> 00:08:37.567
[metal detector beeping]

151
00:08:37.615 --> 00:08:40.740
♪♪

152
00:08:47.725 --> 00:08:51.576
♪♪

153
00:08:56.600 --> 00:09:00.443
♪♪

154
00:09:03.042 --> 00:09:04.442
[sighs]

155
00:09:06.710 --> 00:09:10.279
♪♪

156
00:09:19.542 --> 00:09:21.511
Yeah. Tribal police?

157
00:09:22.042 --> 00:09:24.753
Yeah. I was out on your property
this afternoon

158
00:09:24.964 --> 00:09:26.906
and found a dead body

159
00:09:28.018 --> 00:09:29.709
off the old post road.

160
00:09:30.284 --> 00:09:34.776
Out in the scrub. just past
the Oasis Motel Billboard.

161
00:09:35.518 --> 00:09:37.284
I was out
with my metal detector.

162
00:09:37.347 --> 00:09:39.180
looking for arrowheads.

163
00:09:40.761 --> 00:09:42.292
No. I don't want
to give my name.

164
00:09:42.370 --> 00:09:44.120
I-I-I was trespassing.

165
00:09:44.206 --> 00:09:46.719
Look. y-you'd better
send someone out there

166
00:09:46.767 --> 00:09:49.568
to find him
before the coyotes do.

167
00:09:51.522 --> 00:09:59.522
♪♪

168
00:10:01.632 --> 00:10:07.872
♪♪

169
00:10:08.054 --> 00:10:12.093
Over here. I've recorded
the location of the incident.

170
00:10:12.187 --> 00:10:15.819
that is where I was physically
when it began.

171
00:10:15.929 --> 00:10:18.804
This column
gives a proximate origin...

172
00:10:18.968 --> 00:10:21.866
Uh. and as you can see.
uh. much of time.

173
00:10:21.937 --> 00:10:24.319
I couldn't be sure.
so I just wrote "ambient."

174
00:10:24.687 --> 00:10:26.202
Um. and. of course.
I've recorded

175
00:10:26.296 --> 00:10:29.155
the. uh. times
and dosages of the medicine.

176
00:10:29.241 --> 00:10:31.187
This is very impressive.
Charles.

177
00:10:31.280 --> 00:10:33.339
And look at the trend!

178
00:10:34.499 --> 00:10:38.046
Day one. pain of 7 and 8.
even 8.5.

179
00:10:38.202 --> 00:10:40.835
Day three. nothing higher
than five and a quarter.

180
00:10:40.928 --> 00:10:41.928
And now...

181
00:10:42.015 --> 00:10:43.553
It's all 3s and 4s.

182
00:10:44.695 --> 00:10:45.847
Later in the session.

183
00:10:45.895 --> 00:10:47.436
I'd like
to give you some exercises

184
00:10:47.484 --> 00:10:49.335
and strategies
that might help even more.

185
00:10:49.413 --> 00:10:50.976
I'm all ears.

186
00:10:52.101 --> 00:10:53.999
How do you see your next steps?

187
00:10:54.476 --> 00:10:57.460
Well. clearly.
with this kind of improvement.

188
00:10:57.668 --> 00:11:00.765
it won't be long before
I'm back to work full time.

189
00:11:00.843 --> 00:11:02.617
with no accommodations.

190
00:11:02.928 --> 00:11:05.053
And then. soon after.
I want to get back into court.

191
00:11:05.163 --> 00:11:07.787
I haven't argued a case
in almost three years.

192
00:11:07.920 --> 00:11:09.428
so that's next.

193
00:11:10.358 --> 00:11:13.212
And I'm gonna get these lights
turned back on.

194
00:11:13.733 --> 00:11:16.248
I want this house
to be full of music.

195
00:11:16.522 --> 00:11:18.017
I want to have a dinner party...

196
00:11:18.451 --> 00:11:20.100
Oh. hell. no.
[Chuckles]

197
00:11:20.350 --> 00:11:21.616
A great. big celebration.

198
00:11:21.717 --> 00:11:23.280
I want a hundred people in here.

199
00:11:23.350 --> 00:11:25.076
Spilling out onto the lawn...

200
00:11:25.272 --> 00:11:28.506
I want caterers and a full bar.

201
00:11:29.123 --> 00:11:32.686
I want to be surrounded
by friends and colleagues.

202
00:11:33.030 --> 00:11:34.186
That's stirring.

203
00:11:34.264 --> 00:11:36.241
[Chuckles]
Those are excellent goals.

204
00:11:36.569 --> 00:11:38.178
Doctor. I wouldn't have believed

205
00:11:38.248 --> 00:11:41.076
I could come so far so quickly.

206
00:11:41.459 --> 00:11:44.311
And I have to give you
the lion's share of the credit.

207
00:11:44.444 --> 00:11:46.553
Well. it's remarkable.

208
00:11:47.006 --> 00:11:49.178
But Rome wasn't built in a day.

209
00:11:49.389 --> 00:11:51.161
I know rushing forward
may be tempting.

210
00:11:51.209 --> 00:11:53.201
but it's important
to give yourself time.

211
00:11:53.249 --> 00:11:54.084
Mm.

212
00:11:54.132 --> 00:11:57.717
You've just begun a journey
that could take years.

213
00:11:59.178 --> 00:12:00.482
Well. I suppose.

214
00:12:00.530 --> 00:12:03.897
But. um. surely you'd admit
that every case is different?

215
00:12:03.959 --> 00:12:05.053
Of course.

216
00:12:05.101 --> 00:12:08.530
Then perhaps. uh.
my recovery might be speedier

217
00:12:08.578 --> 00:12:09.920
than your
Run-of-the-Mill patient.

218
00:12:09.968 --> 00:12:11.037
Isn't that possible?

219
00:12:11.085 --> 00:12:13.287
I'm just cautioning you
not to push yourself too hard.

220
00:12:13.358 --> 00:12:14.686
- Mm.
- I know.

221
00:12:15.310 --> 00:12:16.951
Appreciate every step forward.

222
00:12:17.037 --> 00:12:19.326
but modulate your expectations.

223
00:12:19.521 --> 00:12:21.881
Yes. absolutely.

224
00:12:23.623 --> 00:12:25.521
Let's talk about
the night you first called me.

225
00:12:25.608 --> 00:12:27.600
- Mm.
- You sounded very distressed.

226
00:12:27.717 --> 00:12:28.943
I was.

227
00:12:29.092 --> 00:12:31.412
Using a telephone must have been
difficult for you.

228
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:32.709
[Sighs]

229
00:12:32.787 --> 00:12:34.833
I had to walk 10 blocks
to a pay phone.

230
00:12:34.881 --> 00:12:36.630
That was
extremely uncomfortable.

231
00:12:36.678 --> 00:12:38.239
P-probably almost a 9.

232
00:12:38.287 --> 00:12:39.676
[inhales sharply. clears throat]

233
00:12:39.724 --> 00:12:42.787
What made it so important
to talk to me that night?

234
00:12:43.200 --> 00:12:44.864
[Sighs]

235
00:12:45.216 --> 00:12:47.514
I'd had an incident.

236
00:12:47.833 --> 00:12:51.021
A very public incident.

237
00:12:51.803 --> 00:12:54.576
Perhaps the worst experience
of my life.

238
00:12:57.809 --> 00:12:58.974
[Sighs]

239
00:12:59.030 --> 00:13:02.576
It was proven to me. in public.

240
00:13:02.644 --> 00:13:04.362
And beyond
the shadow of a doubt.

241
00:13:04.433 --> 00:13:09.073
that there was a battery...
a fully charged battery...

242
00:13:09.800 --> 00:13:13.566
Almost next to my skin for
the better part of two hours.

243
00:13:14.827 --> 00:13:16.761
And I felt nothing.

244
00:13:19.407 --> 00:13:22.034
What does that mean to you?

245
00:13:23.716 --> 00:13:24.886
[Clicks tongue]

246
00:13:24.934 --> 00:13:26.232
[Inhales deeply]

247
00:13:26.280 --> 00:13:28.435
This condition...

248
00:13:29.652 --> 00:13:31.948
to me.
it's as real as that chair.

249
00:13:32.073 --> 00:13:33.456
It's as real as this house.

250
00:13:33.558 --> 00:13:35.253
It's as real as you.

251
00:13:35.793 --> 00:13:37.027
But...

252
00:13:38.581 --> 00:13:40.696
What if it's not?

253
00:13:42.191 --> 00:13:44.948
What if it's all in my head?

254
00:13:45.936 --> 00:13:48.917
And if that's true...

255
00:13:49.643 --> 00:13:51.902
If it's not real...

256
00:13:54.487 --> 00:13:57.379
Then what have I done?

257
00:13:59.069 --> 00:14:02.069
[Clock ticking]

258
00:14:04.355 --> 00:14:05.757
It's all in the storyboards.

259
00:14:05.817 --> 00:14:07.317
Get set for the master shot.

260
00:14:07.382 --> 00:14:08.781
Okay.

261
00:14:09.085 --> 00:14:10.562
Lookin' good!

262
00:14:10.631 --> 00:14:12.764
- We about ready?
- Just about.

263
00:14:12.963 --> 00:14:14.070
I gotta hand it to you.

264
00:14:14.118 --> 00:14:16.202
[Chuckling] I mean.
this is the busiest weekday

265
