You were fine.

593
00:28:59.271 --> 00:29:01.271
Uh. that was<i> Tuesday.</i>

594
00:29:01.513 --> 00:29:03.207
You picked up clean clothes.

595
00:29:03.255 --> 00:29:05.288
'Member?

596
00:29:05.370 --> 00:29:07.937
Did you go to the doctor?

597
00:29:08.887 --> 00:29:11.801
Oh. it's... it's not
as bad as it looks.

598
00:29:11.864 --> 00:29:13.137
I just need to rest it.

599
00:29:13.244 --> 00:29:14.577
It'll be fine.

600
00:29:15.035 --> 00:29:16.270
Look on the desk.

601
00:29:16.372 --> 00:29:18.639
There's something for you.

602
00:29:20.219 --> 00:29:21.567
Yeah. that.

603
00:29:22.271 --> 00:29:24.138
Open it.

604
00:29:25.764 --> 00:29:27.317
That's my half.

605
00:29:27.750 --> 00:29:29.443
It's good
for the next six weeks.

606
00:29:29.491 --> 00:29:30.568
[Inhales sharply]

607
00:29:30.627 --> 00:29:33.138
So at least we can
stop talking about<i> that.</i>

608
00:29:33.299 --> 00:29:34.459
Jimmy. I wasn't...

609
00:29:34.513 --> 00:29:36.916
- just take it
- So we're square. all right?

610
00:29:38.858 --> 00:29:40.159
Okay.

611
00:29:41.252 --> 00:29:42.465
Sorry.

612
00:29:42.893 --> 00:29:44.030
Just...

613
00:29:44.080 --> 00:29:47.143
My back hurts like hell.
and. uh...

614
00:29:47.356 --> 00:29:50.190
People suck.

615
00:29:54.866 --> 00:29:57.273
Jimmy. you...

616
00:29:57.998 --> 00:30:00.340
You don't have to
push yourself like this.

617
00:30:03.984 --> 00:30:05.812
You could rest.
[Sighs] [Music stops]

618
00:30:06.366 --> 00:30:07.598
Let your back heal.

619
00:30:08.180 --> 00:30:09.601
And then
you go to community service

620
00:30:09.649 --> 00:30:10.827
And get it over with.

621
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:12.249
Take some time.

622
00:30:12.303 --> 00:30:13.960
Plan your next move.

623
00:30:14.139 --> 00:30:15.405
Meaning...?

624
00:30:15.579 --> 00:30:16.945
I'm saying...

625
00:30:17.679 --> 00:30:19.663
I could cover our expenses
for a while.

626
00:30:19.711 --> 00:30:21.453
- Kim. you got the cash in your hand.
- Yeah. I know. but...

627
00:30:21.500 --> 00:30:23.405
- So why are we talking about this?
- All I'm saying is

628
00:30:23.452 --> 00:30:25.106
I looked at the numbers.
and I<i> can</i> carry us.

629
00:30:25.153 --> 00:30:28.405
Not forever. but at least until
you're back to 100%.

630
00:30:28.648 --> 00:30:30.905
I appreciate the thought.
but no.

631
00:30:31.249 --> 00:30:33.335
I'll do what I have to do
to take care of my half.

632
00:30:33.386 --> 00:30:35.538
You do what you have to do
to take care of yours.

633
00:30:35.609 --> 00:30:37.855
End of story. [Sighs]

634
00:30:40.950 --> 00:30:42.263
Okay.

635
00:30:44.844 --> 00:30:47.043
[Guitar playing]

636
00:30:47.196 --> 00:30:49.880
I mean. you believe me. right?

637
00:30:51.363 --> 00:30:53.163
Yes.

638
00:30:57.336 --> 00:30:59.570
Feel better. Jimmy.

639
00:31:09.412 --> 00:31:11.934
